# Confident AI Documentation Style Guide

This project uses Fern for documentation. Follow these patterns and best practices when creating or editing documentation.

## Page Structure

Every documentation page must follow this structure:

```mdx
---
subtitle: Brief description of the page content
slug: path/to/page
description: Optional SEO description
---

## Overview

[High-level explanation of what the page covers - 1-3 paragraphs]

[Main content sections...]

## Next Steps

[Links to related/following content using CardGroup]
```

### Frontmatter Rules

- `subtitle`: Required. Short description that appears below the title.
- `slug`: Required. Clean URL path (e.g., `llm-evaluation/quickstart`).
- `description`: Optional. Used for SEO.
- `title`: Only use when different from the sidebar navigation name.

## Components

### Callouts

Use these callout components appropriately:

| Component   | When to Use                                          |
| ----------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| `<Note>`    | General information, clarifications, tips            |
| `<Tip>`     | Pro tips, optional enhancements, best practices      |
| `<Warning>` | Prerequisites, important cautions, potential issues  |
| `<Info>`    | Technical clarifications, implementation details     |
| `<Success>` | Short confirmations, highlights, completion messages |

```mdx
<Note>Content here. Can include [links](/path) and **formatting**.</Note>

<Tip title="Optional Title" icon="leaf">
  Tips can have titles and icons.
</Tip>

<Warning>Prerequisites or cautions go here.</Warning>
```

### Cards

Use `<CardGroup>` with `<Card>` for feature showcases and navigation:

```mdx
<CardGroup cols={2}>
  <Card
    title="Card Title"
    icon="icon-name"
    iconType="solid"
    href="/optional/link"
  >
    - Bullet point features
    - Another feature

    **Suitable for:** Target audience description

  </Card>
</CardGroup>
```

Rules:

- Use `cols={2}` for side-by-side comparisons (Local vs Remote pattern)
- Use `cols={3}` for feature overviews
- Include "**Suitable for:**" line when comparing options
- Use Font Awesome icons (e.g., `laptop`, `cloud`, `flask-vial`)

### Tabs

Use `<Tabs>` for language/platform variations:

````mdx
<Tabs>
  <Tab title="Python" language="python">
    ```python # Python code ```
  </Tab>
  <Tab title="TypeScript" language="typescript">
    ```typescript // TypeScript code ```
  </Tab>
  <Tab title="curL" language="curl">
    <EndpointRequestSnippet endpoint="GET /v1/endpoint" />
  </Tab>
</Tabs>
````

Rules:

- Order: Python → TypeScript → cURL (when showing SDK examples)
- Use `language` attribute on Tab components
- Nest Tabs when showing UI vs Code alternatives

### Steps

Use `<Steps>` for tutorials and quickstarts:

````mdx
<Steps>
  <Step title="Step Title">
    Step content here. ```bash # Commands or code ```
  </Step>
  <Step title="Next Step">
    More content. End with confirmation: ✅ Done. You just completed [action].
  </Step>
</Steps>
````

### Media

Use `<Frame>` for images and videos:

```mdx
<Frame caption="Descriptive Caption" background="subtle">
  <video
    autoPlay
    loop
    muted
    src="https://confident-docs.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/video.mp4"
    type="video/mp4"
  />
</Frame>

<Frame caption="Image Caption">
  <img src="https://confident-docs.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/image.png" />
</Frame>
```

### Accordions (FAQs)

```mdx
<AccordionGroup>
  <Accordion title="Question here?">
    Answer content with [links](/path) if needed.
  </Accordion>
</AccordionGroup>
```

### Code Blocks

````mdx
```python main.py {6,17}
# Include filename after language
# Use {lineNumbers} to highlight important lines
from deepeval import evaluate
```
````

For multiple related code snippets:

````mdx
<CodeBlocks>
  ```bash title="Option 1"
  export API_KEY=value
````

```python title="Option 2"
configure(api_key="value")
```

</CodeBlocks>
```

### Parameter Documentation

```mdx
<ParamField path="param_name" type="string" required>
  Description of the parameter.
</ParamField>

<ParamField path="optional_param" type="number" default={0.5}>
  Description with default value.
</ParamField>
```

